    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-26T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-26T19:00:00-05:00" n="735"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d735">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">822.5151/4–2646: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Shaw</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-26T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 26, 1946—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>176. <gloss target="#t_urtel1">Urtel</gloss> 218 Apr. 25. You are authorized in
                    your discretion either to make formal protest or other representations or
                    both.</p>
                <p>Protest should be based on commitments by <gloss target="#t_Ec1">Ec</gloss> Govt
                    on basis of which we drastically reduced <gloss target="#t_PL1">PL</gloss> and
                    should express surprise or disappointment that in light of excellent cooperation
                    in these matters in past <gloss target="#t_Ec1">Ec</gloss> Govt should take this
                    action without offering us opportunity to give our views and furnish evidence
                    concerning cases. Note should not imply we have intransigent views with respect
                    unblocking every and all persons now blocked but should stress we feel
                    unblocking should only occur after careful review of all facts and not on
                    nationality basis, alone.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_reur1">Reur</gloss> telephone conversation today with Scotten,
                    Embassy has full evidence why funds in question should not be unblocked.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
